claim.claim-text:
1. A valve, comprising in combination:
an inlet housing;
an outlet housing;
an elastomeric valve element having a generally dome-shaped configuration with a central integral stem positioned substantially concentrically therewith;
said inlet housing and said outlet housing being fastened together at a joint with said elastomeric valve element positioned therein; and
said valve element including a plurality of longitudinal ribs formed along an outer annular periphery of a lower end of said dome-shaped configuration in engagement with said outlet housing that define flow channels that allow fluid flow from across an upper surface of said dome-shaped configuration through said flow channels.

12. A valve, comprising in combination:
an inlet housing;
an outlet housing, said outlet housing comprising a plurality of castellations formed along an inner annular periphery of said outlet housing that define flow channels;
an elastomeric valve element having a generally dome-shaped configuration with a central integral stem positioned substantially concentrically therewith, a lower edge of said dome-shaped configuration of said valve element being juxtapositioned against upper surfaces of the castellations;
said inlet housing and said outlet housing being fastened together at a joint with said elastomeric valve element positioned therein; and
said valve element including a plurality of longitudinal ribs formed along an outer annular periphery of a lower end of said dome-shaped configuration that define flow channels that allow fluid flow from across an upper surface of said dome-shaped configuration through said flow channels, the relative annular spacing and size of said castellations being different from the annular spacing and size of said longitudinal ribs such that fluid flow is allowed through said flow channels defined by said longitudinal ribs and said flow channels defined by said castellations.

14. A valve, comprising in combination:
an inlet housing;
an outlet housing;
an elastomeric valve element having a generally dome-shaped configuration with a central integral stem positioned substantially concentrically therewith;
said inlet housing and said outlet housing being fastened together at a joint with said elastomeric valve element positioned therein; and
said valve element including a plurality of longitudinal ribs formed along an outer annular periphery of a lower end of said dome-shaped configuration that define flow channels that allow fluid flow from across an upper surface of said dome-shaped configuration through said flow channels, said valve element further including a plurality of ribs positioned longitudinally along the length of said stem.

15. A valve, comprising in combination:
an inlet housing;
an outlet housing;
an elastomeric valve element having a generally dome-shaped configuration with a central integral stem positioned substantially concentrically therewith;
said inlet housing and said outlet housing being fastened together at a joint with said elastomeric valve element positioned therein; and
said valve element including a plurality of longitudinal ribs formed along an outer annular periphery of a lower end of said dome-shaped configuration that define flow channels that allow fluid flow from across an upper surface of said dome-shaped configuration through said flow channels, said valve element comprising a at least two annular reliefs formed in said dome-shaped configuration to allow easier flexing when said valve element is opened, said reliefs being positioned concentrically in the underside said dome-shaped configuration.
